title: [Western Waterway]
description: Tapering off towards the east, the water laps about a small sandbar that leads up to an ebon-hued cliff.  Tendrils of vine drape from the peak, blanketing much of the wall.  Worn away by eons of rain and wind, a narrow crack breaks the surface.
paths: Obvious paths: north, northeast, southeast, south, southwest, west, northwest
